						<summary>

						<p>On a granite pillar set up in front of the Śiva temple on the bank of the Kṛishṇā.</p>						

						<p>[Kākatīya Gaṇapatidēva-mahārāja].</p>						

						<p>Dated in <hi rend="italic">Saumya, Phālguna,</hi> ba. 11.</p>						

						<p>Seems to record the gift of the village Taḍimaḍa in Kanna-munnūru by Vēgeyadēva, Mandaya and Gaṇapaya, who are styled <hi rend="italic">gandhahasti-gajasāhiṇis</hi> for the merit of Kākatīśvara Gaṇapatidēvamahārāja. The gift-village was entrusted to Bhāvabrahma-gurudēva Sahadēva.</p>						

						</summary>
